SIMPLE: settee
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Settee
<hw>Set*tee"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Set</er>;
cf. <er>Settle</er> a seat.]</ety> <def>A long seat with a back, -- made
to accommodate several persons at once.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Settee</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Settee
<hw>Set*tee"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>sc⟦eacute⟧tie</ets>,
<ets>scitie</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A vessel with a very
long, sharp prow, carrying two or three masts with lateen sails, -- used
in the Mediterranean.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>setee</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Setter</ent>⟦br⟧
